description.plain:
Another song based on a real event, according to Jordan. Edward Benz had a schizophrenic son who took pills to keep his illness under control. One day he decided to stop taking the pills, and he went mad, shutting himself into his house. His father came, and when he opened the door with the key, his son assaulted him with a knife, stabbing him (maybe “27 times” is the number of times his son stabbed him?).

The song is structured in 3 different times:
- the time present, when the protagonist of the album remembers the story of Edward Benz and his son and writes some considerations upon the subject;
- the time (remembered in the present) when he met Edward Benz to fix his broken door, and Edward told him his sad story;
- the time (told in Ed’s story the day he met the protagonist) when the tragic events occurred.

